OL,3,CThrill-seeking storm chaser says 'I
OL,4,Ccan't imagine I'll ever be frightened'
OL,6,F"You need certain conditions to
OL,7,Fproduce a thunderstorm and a
OL,8,Fsupercell. And when supercells
OL,9,Feventually do form, they look like
OL,10,Fgigantic motherships in front of you
OL,11,Fand it causes rotations of the wind.
OL,13,F"You need a lot of moisture in the
OL,14,Fair. You need cold and warm fronts to
OL,15,Fhit each other. It causes a rotation
OL,16,Fin the clouds. And then lo and behold,
OL,17,Fsometimes if you're lucky, a tornado
OL,18,Fdrops."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/7
