OL,3,CThrill-seeking storm chaser says 'I
OL,4,Ccan't imagine I'll ever be frightened'
OL,6,FThe team works alongside a
OL,7,Fclimatologist and, while they are
OL,8,Fnever in the eye of the storm, they
OL,9,Fare always on its tail.
OL,11,FBut Abbi said she does not feel the
OL,12,Ffear. Instead, she is just in awe of
OL,13,Fthe "power of nature".
OL,15,F"I don't find it scary," she added.
OL,16,F"I'm sure some people would. And I
OL,17,Fthink the locals we meet think we're
OL,18,Fcrazy for coming out all of this way
OL,19,Fto chase the weather, but I find it
OL,20,Fexhilarating."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/7
